w ways to help a Manastone re-enter main steam Everquest.<br><br>First off, there drops: No, not God or Dragon drops...I would like a few more people to see this item and if its on a MOB that high there will be very little chance of that happening so we move them to a high level area off a farely tuff MOB maybe the new CT or even Luclin...somewhere just about anyone can have a chance of getting one(anyone being the ones that it will be restriced to).<br><br>Next they need to be LORE or NO DROP...I'd rather see NO DROP because it could cut down on camping, for the most part anyway, there will always be some out there abusing something one way or another but a NO DROP item could help in the camp area..unless you run across the high end guild that wants one for there level 3 Wizard...thats where  the next idea comes to mind.<br><br>A level restriction. Unlike the melee weapons, this item will have a level restriction on it. You need to be 35 plus(or something like that) to use it so there is very little chance of that guild mentioned above wanting one for that level 3 Wizard to help him/her to be power leveled any faster then normal and unlike the melee screw up,the level restriction would keep it in check and not let it get out of hand to the point Caster would become God-like in there ability to kill...and speaking of Casters..<br><br>It would be useable by the INT casters only...sorry Priest-classes but I'm sure you see why Verant is scared of them begin used by you n the first place and why they needed to stop there influx...though why it took seven months AFTER the release of the game to do that is still a mystery to me but hey....<br><br>Next is the tricky part.....if, as someone stated, it had some restrictions on it it could re-enter the world and not go overboard in its abuse. Where its used really dosen't matter, Old world, Planes, The Moon there all the same more or less, what needs to be looked at is HOW there used, not where.<br><br>Putting a cast time on it is bad...unless the ratio is more then 3:1...maybe 300:100 with a 3 second cast time or even, as here someone stated, a stunn or spell effect to keep its use below abuse(hey that rhymes)..it can't be used while you have a rez effect in place. <br><br>I really think Verant wants a Manastone-type of item out there but the ones that they stated with are a bit over board...hence the Mana robe but even there they are worried..damn rare from what I've heard and the 3 second cast time to get the old 3:1 ratio stinks in my opinion...there are ways to fix just about anything even if you have to piss off a few players that refuse to see the abuse an item will bring(sorry but Clerics come to mind here) do it....don't let the rest of the game players suffer because of it...doing that is like I said...throwing the baby out with the bath water. Thanks and take care. <p>Shaithin, The NPC</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Moderator</font></td></tr></table><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Verant's #1 Fanboy</font></td></tr></table></span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/13/02 6:00:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=927.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manastones..Christ isn't there SOME